<!-- Goal (RoboSub 2026 pre-qual): fully autonomous — submerge (hold 1m - 1.3m) & start 3 m behind the Gate → pass
through the Gate → circle the Marker (10 m beyond) → pass back through the Gate, without breaching,
recorded continuously, nothing floating.

DEAD-RECKONED. Heading + depth hold run continuously in the controller; this tree only sets targets,
toggles open-loop surge, and times transitions. EVERY number below is a port calibrate the run
pool-side by editing this file, no rebuild:
  surge_thrust: open-loop forward thrust pct (distance ~= thrust x duration)
  duration_s: seconds of surge for each leg (gate / marker / box leg / back)
  depth: hold depth in metres (+down)
  relative_yaw_deg + timeout_s: the four box corners (~90 deg each) -->

<root BTCPP_format="4" main_tree_to_execute="PreQualRun">
    <BehaviorTree ID="PreQualRun">
        <Sequence name="PreQualRun">
            <!-- Submerge and confirm we have settled before driving forward. -->
            <Submerge depth="1.2" />
            <HoldDepthStable target_depth="1.2" tolerance="0.1" timeout_s="10.0" />

            <!-- Clear the 3 m run-up + the 2 m gate. -->
            <Surge name="SurgeThroughGate" surge_thrust="40" duration_s="6.0" />

            <!-- Drive the ~10 m out to the marker. -->
            <Surge name="SurgeToMarker" surge_thrust="40" duration_s="12.0" />

            <!-- Box around the marker: 4 x (turn 90 deg, then drive one leg).
                 4 x 90 = 360, so we exit the box at the SAME heading we entered
                 it with (still pointing away from the gate) and roughly back at
                 the marker. -->
            <Repeat num_cycles="4">
                <Sequence name="BoxLeg">
                    <Turn relative_yaw_deg="90" heading_tolerance_deg="8.0" timeout_s="8.0" />
                    <Surge name="SurgeLeg" surge_thrust="40" duration_s="4.0" />
                </Sequence>
            </Repeat>

            <!-- Turn around to FACE the gate before driving back. Without this,
                 "surge forward" below would drive further away from the gate
                 (the box left us pointing marker-ward). 180 in one go sits on the
                 +-180 wrap seam; if it picks the turn direction unreliably, split
                 into two relative_yaw_deg="90" Turns. -->
            <Turn name="TurnAround" relative_yaw_deg="180" heading_tolerance_deg="8.0" timeout_s="10.0" />

            <!-- Back through the gate. This starts at the MARKER now, so it must
                 cover the full marker -> gate distance (~10 m) plus clearance,
                 not just a short hop. Calibrate >= SurgeToMarker. -->
            <Surge name="SurgeBackThroughGate" surge_thrust="40" duration_s="14.0" />

            <!-- Surface: depth target 0, surge off. -->
            <Surface />
        </Sequence>
    </BehaviorTree>
</root>
